"You'll find that you miss exhales in reverb
and thrice daily sunrise of satellites,"
it hummed through cosmic glows of far flung fogs,
where ionised dust darkly twist and turn
in tendrils with a thoughtless inertia,
spinning because it was spinning before.
"Eternal freefall like moon in orbit,
apart from thermodynamic chaos,
you found your home in upper vacancies."

The Spaceman fell from high-up stratosphere,
so heat had tunneled through ortho-fabrics.
Though braced and boldened, naught did atmos fear
neoprene and aramid synthetics
(As with the ortho-personality
which once had channeled, from hopeless despair
and built-up cynical mentality,
alleged inability to care).
Despite worn shells, this was a faceless fall;
pity for him, his helmet reflects all.
A MANIFESTO OF NODES AND CONNECTORS
Hidden was broken asceticism
behind unsettled snowy mounds, like graves
of the thousand summers that never came
to the night-side of the Ever-Sunward.
Spaceman, having taken a mourning knee
so as to bring fight to pulling parachute
that follows the light-side sourced one-way wind,
sought the sun to keep the stars from his mind -
for should he look up and reflect the stars,
he'd do the same for the spaces between.
Among summer graves Spaceman grasped at strings
which puppeteered him back, set the sun.
What might have been sights that twilight oft brings
showed something walking out of void and none
like a subtraction to reality.
Spaceman saw, straight through horizon to space,
shaped-reflection of actuality,
a being that stayed cosmos from it's place
walked on legs of empty, it moved closer,
resting hand of nothing on his shoulder.
Unhelmed, he was, where stars glint in wet eyes,
No more appearing like something other.
Himself because he can now realise
a core importance that's now his tether.
"There are axioms of truth you can find -
some little pockets of stability
- which fight breakdowns of the entropic kind
But bring into you a fragility.
I want to think I know what comes, but then...
None can remember what's yet to happen"
During distracting flashing lights it left,
(Both the Empty and Spaceman's confidence
in his satisfaction with unknown chance
and his proclamation of common sense).
Strobe lights for warning the unpredicted,
with continuous tracks propelling it,
carries forces and weapons that fight off
nondeterministic, frightening things.
From the strings of the 'chute to 'cuffs on wrist
News he brings must be muted till secure.
